A 44-year-old man is suspected of using a hammer to bludgeon to death his girlfriend and her adult daughter because he believed they were 'witches' and performing voodoo on him, law enforcement sources told the New York Post.

Carlos Amarillo was taken into custody early Wednesday morning after police found the dead bodies of girlfriend Estrella Castaneda, 56, and her 25-year-old daughter Lina in the Queens, New York home the three shared.

Lina was mother herself to a 7-year-old daughter who was home at the time but uninjured in the attack and is now in protective custody. Sources told WABC that she slept through the brutal killings. 

